{"title":"Every men’s UCI WorldTour race ranked: From the Tour de France to the Tour Down Under","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/worldtour-race-ranked-men","date":1715617033000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/worldtour-race-ranked-men\">Every men’s UCI WorldTour race ranked: From the Tour de France to the Tour Down Under</a></p>\n\n<p>The UCI WorldTour is the top tier of professional cycling. In the men’s calendar, there are 35 races on the UCI WorldTour level as of 2024. For the women’s, there are 27. These vary from the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a> all the way down to the Tour of Guangxi in China. The men’s WorldTour race line-up has changed a lot through the years (we miss you, Tour of California). However, the WorldTour is the closest cycling comes to having its own Premier League – at least until <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/saudi-pro-cycling-league\" target=\"_blank\">Saudi Arabia takes over</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As fans of cycling, we enjoy a bit of competition. Why not take this to an extreme and pit the competitions themselves against one another? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ranking WorldTour races is like comparing apples and pears. Every men’s WorldTour race has its own vibe, of course, and these will play into the ranking on this list. On top of this, the route, prestige and recent race results will also influence the outcome of this highly subjective (and illustrious) classification. Above all, it’s all just a bit of fun and not meant to be taken too seriously.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-mens-cycling-2024\">Opinion: Men’s cycling has never been more bleak for fans</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-monument-ranking\">Every Tadej Pogačar Monument performance ranked</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mathieu-van-der-poel-monument-ranked\">Every Mathieu van der Poel Monument performance ranked</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024 route announced: What will riders face on the road from Florence to Nice?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1740048607-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Lower Rankings</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>34. Cadel Evans Great Ocean Road Race</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>I don’t believe in the mentality of ‘build it and they will come’.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>33. Tour of Guangxi</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Have you ever watched a stage of this race? I dare you to name any GC winner.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>32. Tour Down Under</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As a European, I am not nocturnal enough to watch this.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>31. Eschborn Frankfurt</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s nice that Germany has a WorldTour race, but let’s try and do better.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1946576130-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Peter Mundy/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>30. BEMER Cyclassics</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>See above.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>29. Tour de Suisse</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Hold a race concurrently with the Dauphiné at your own peril.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>28. Volta Ciclista a Catalunya</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>March has better stage races.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>27. UAE Tour</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Pros: Jebel Hafeet. Cons: hours of sandy helicopter shots, excessive sprint stages and a host nation with a poor human rights record. Wait, maybe I should revise this ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2037786732-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>26. Classic Brugge De Panne</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>I miss the old 3 days we used to get. Now it’s just a flash in De Panne.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>25. Itzulia Basque Country</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s hard to stand out during the meaty Classics week. This race tries, but it doesn’t have enough bite to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>24. La Flèche Wallonne</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Mur de Huy is decent, I guess.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>23. Gent-Wevelgem</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A glorified sprinter’s Classic under the guise of a cobbled affair? No, thank you.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2150529203-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Luc Claessen/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>22. Tour de Romandie</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>No one is going to take you seriously if Ethan Hayter is poaching bunch sprints year-on-year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>21. Vuelta a España </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This Grand Tour is an afterthought. As much as I admire <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/primoz-roglic\" target=\"_blank\">Primož Roglič</a>, that’s not enough to salvage some places on the list.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>20. Donostia San Sebastian Klasikoa</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The ‘ol Tony Gallopin exhibition race. The Klasikoa serves up some much-needed one-day action in the summertime. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>19. Giro di Lombardia</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yikes, the ‘race of the falling leaves’ is a chore to get through. It’s only in the top 20 because of its Monument status.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"606\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-970x606.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-970x606.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-300x188.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-768x480.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-750x469.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited-1140x713.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/liegebastogne23-hill-min-edited.png 1280w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Maxime Delobel</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>18. Liège-Bastogne-Liège</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>By this point in the year, I’m tired of spending my Sunday afternoons watching Benelux countryside.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>17. Tirreno-Adriatico</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The only race where the trophy is a big barbecue fork. A solid week-long stage race with plenty of spice. Tirreno should end with a time-trial though. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>16. E3 Saxo Classic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Homophobic tweets and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/is-it-time-to-switch-off-in-protest-against-sexism\" target=\"_blank\">sexist posters</a> aside, E3 is usually a good race. However, it feels all too much like a bootleg Tour of Flanders. The race also finishes on a new-build housing estate, which takes away from the oomph of the Classics magic.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>15. Dwaars door Vlaanderen</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The forgotten child of the Flemish Classics, Dwaars door Vlaanderen – which literally translates to ‘All Around Flanders’ (terrible name) – feels like a tray of Flemish canapés. Serving wind, cobbles, bad weather and <em>grinta </em>in spades, this one-day race is the bohemian alternative to the Ronde.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-970x683.jpg\" alt=\"Dylan van Baarle climbs on the cobbles surrounded by cheering fans on the Kapelmuur\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-970x683.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-300x211.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-768x541.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-1536x1082.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-2048x1443.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-750x528.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/02/Dylan-van-Baarle-on-Kapelmuur-by-Jasper-JAcobs-Getty-1140x803.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption>Jasper Jacobs/Belga Mag/AFP via Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>14. Omloop Het Nieuwsblad</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Oh boy, this one is a humdinger. The real start to the Classics.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>13. Critérium du Dauphiné</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you like the Alps, you’re going to love the Dauphiné. Slotted right before the Tour, the Dauphiné is the last chance for the yellow jersey contenders to shine and narrow their odds of Tour glory. I’ll be honest, however, the Dauphiné is more often than not an omen of domination to come.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>12. Paris-Nice</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The mini Tour de France, Paris-Nice oozes class. Serving as the real season opener, Paris-Nice is a stage race that offers it all. The final stage around Nice promises nothing but action all the way to the finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>11. Bretagne Classic – Ouest-France</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>I will fight tooth and nail for this race’s WorldTour status. Expect the unexpected in Brittany. The rolling profile makes for a fierce race that only a primary school paper fortune teller could predict.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>10. Milan-San Remo</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/GettyImages-2082108053.jpg 1890w\" /><figcaption>Marco Bertorello/AFP via Getty</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we’re talking. Milan-San Remo guarantees, and I mean guarantees, the wildest 20 minutes of cycling you’ll watch on the calendar. The relentless, and sometimes desperate, attacks both on and off the Poggio make for fascinating racing as everyone tries to win the toughest race to predict on the cycling calendar. Whether you’re a sprinter, Grand Tour champion or punchy wildcard, you have a chance of taking La Classicissima.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>9. Amstel Gold Race</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-2148605037-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Vincent Kalut/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Oh Amstel, how we love you so dearly. Overshadowed by its Monument brothers and sisters, Amstel Gold is a precious day in the cycling calendar. Looking past the obvious <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/classics-power-play-mathieu-van-der-poels-incredible-amstel-gold-winning-power-data\" target=\"_blank\">2019 case study</a>, Amstel has dished up some stellar editions over the years, from the epic Van Aert-Pidcock-Schachmann skirmish to Gasparotto’s throwback in 2016, Amstel Gold is the GOAT of the Ardennes. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>8. Tour de Pologne</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1592248697-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Controversial, I know, but the Tour of Poland is a cult classic. The Polish race is an underdog sandwiched between Grand Tour titans. The sun-drenched golden hour broadcasts during the long August afternoons may hold a special place in my heart, but this race is overlooked for no good reason. With rolling profiles and sprints galore, the Tour of Poland is a rogue race to predict, filled with twists and turns. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>I would also like to take this opportunity to shun the appropriation of the French language for races that do not take part in France, and most likely never will.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7. Grands Prixs Cycliste de Québec*</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1672446269-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Dario Belingheri/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Broadcast at night in Europe, the Québec races are the perfect build-up to the World Championships. They also make for great tea-time viewing and could be considered the only race socially acceptable to have a beer while watching on TV. Hills, sprints, whatever – these Canadian classics are worthy of the name. Plus, they are the only North American racing we get nowadays at the WorldTour level. Beggars can’t be choosers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p> *The Montréal and Québec races have been grouped into one position. They are the same, and you can’t tell me otherwise.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>6. Tour de France</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"cyclists in white and yellow grimace as they race up hill\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-2048x1364.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bernard Papon/Pool/GodingImages</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I mean, I can’t place this outside of the top ten in all reality. The Tour de France is cycling. We get all the narratives, protagonists and attention that we could possibly want from the sport. In recent years, the compelling battle between Vingegaard and Pogačar has made for a spellbinding spectacle. Turn the clock back to the 2010s and the Tour de France was more of a chore. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>5. Paris-Roubaix</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Paris-Roubaix-Mens-Race-Gallery-Matt-00041-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York/Matt Grayson</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This was always destined to make it into the top five. Plainly, it would be disrespectful to commit treason against the Queen of the Classics’ name. You already know her well, there’s no need to elaborate any further.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>4. Giro d’Italia</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-1140x761.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-2151563083-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s conveniently forget the underwhelming Giri of the 2020s and remember the golden era of this Grand Tour. The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\" target=\"_blank\">Giro</a> is [usually] a fabulous feast of all the things we crave from a Grand Tour. Set against the backdrop of Italy’s sociocultural and geographical mosaic, the Corsa Rosa guarantees three weeks of unparalleled joy. Besides, the pink jersey is a wonderfully unique leader’s jersey. You could even say that the <em><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\" target=\"_blank\">maglia rosa</a></em> has been fighting toxic masculinity since 1931. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>3. Renewi Tour</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/GettyImages-1642377835-min-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Bas Czerwinski/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Calm down, calm down – let me explain this. The Renewi Tour is an underappreciated force within the WorldTour calendar. I dare to call it the Aston Villa of the WorldTour. Taking place in the cultural heartland of cycling, the Eneco…BinckBank…no, I mean, Renewi Tour holds a special place in all our hearts. The race is a week-long Classic. Ardennes, cobbles, time-trials and sprints, it’s the Grand Tour for those scared of heights. The summertime schedule also means that we get to see cycling in Belgium under clear bright skies (or so we think). Bonus points are also levied by the innovative ‘golden kilometre’. If you don’t know what that is, Google it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2. Strade Bianche</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Strade Bianche vs Palio\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/strade-bianche-palio-08.jpg 1536w\" /><figcaption>David Powell</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Gravel is a fad, but Strade Bianche is a lifestyle. This race is a phenomenon and unrivalled in the cycling calendar. Standing out as a gravel one-day race through beautiful Tuscany, Strade Bianche has become one of modern cycling’s great races. The final climb into Siena only adds to its legend, with the biblical gradients, otherworldly sprints and historic photographs captured on the iconic Via Santa Catarina.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>prodigé</em> of the cycling calendar, Strade Bianche has become a headline act in the cycling zeitgeist within a decade. Bravo!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1. Tour of Flanders</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/tour-of-flanders-2023-grubers-16.jpg 1200w\" /><figcaption>Gruberimages</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking the top spot, it’s the old reliable Tour of Flanders. The Ronde van Vlaanderen – to give it its birth name – is the real queen of the Classics. Screw it, it’s the supreme leader, dictator, American president of the Classics. Cobble kickers, beer tents, rabid fans and passion, the Tour of Flanders is a spectacle in its own right.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The snooze button is rarely touched during the race. It promises fireworks, whether that be on the Kapelmuur or the Paterberg. Sprinkle in the mystique of having the pros walk up the hardest climbs and you have a mythical race on your hands. This is the big cheese – or should I say big <em>kaas</em> – of the Classics calendar. Paris-Roubaix is your frail Granny you have to love unconditionally, whereas Flanders is the fun Grandpa who took you out on his boat.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for the Women’s WorldTour ranking next week.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n  